snippet.textDisplay: Can you guys get director Kerry Conran, who made Sky Captain and the World of Tomorrow? The first digital backlot movie that essentially launched the era of filmmaking with "all" digital backgrounds. Which later led to films like Sin City, The Spirit and 300. It's crazy how he helped pioneer the way effects are used in cinema to this day (like that final battle in Endgame) and most people don't even know his name. Think it'd be cool to get insight from him on the couch.

snippet.textDisplay: Love y'all's videos. Wanted to say my fiance, Jim Orlik, is a VFX lead (specifically Mocap; some environments) on Avatar 2 & 3 at Lightstorm right now, but worked on Thor Ragnorok, Star Wars the Force Awakens, and a ton more. He's worked on Mocap video games, too. It's always so fun to talk with him about all of his good (and bad) experiences since it can get so specific with Motion Capture,  and I'm sure he'd love to come chat. P.S. he has no idea I'm commenting this, so you know.
